profile_positions.description:
In my role, I help the Group Performance Management (GPM Practice) team to bring the Project & Performance Management Tool, I-Nexus, to a higher level in order to help Philips become a high performing organisation. 

The GPM practice owns the so-called Planning- and Performance Cycle (P&PC); the end to end process which gives direction to the organization on when and how to plan and assess (business) progress. Evolutionary changes are made every year to this cycle, both from the content as well as from a cultural change point of view. Next to that, the global GPM network drives the implementation of the Performance Management capability into the organization.

As a GPM analyst, I broadly support the further improvement of the Performance Management processes (P&PC-processes) and the growth in maturity of the Group Performance Management practice itself by:

-Supporting the execution and continuous improvement of the goal cascading process as well as the BMC planning process;

-Driving the creation and maintenance of the required methods, tools and templates; act as supporting expert towards the organization;

-Supporting the ramp up of structural GPM sharing and learning in and outside the GPM-network;

-Facilitating cultural change: drive an entrepreneurial mindset and spirit of teaming up between central businesses and local markets to collaborate and deliver results.

-Supporting the learning organization: perform analytics to recognize drivers of performance across businesses, identify top-performers and facilitate the replication the success in lower-performing areas;

-Executing (continuous improvement projects) within the Group Performance Management. 

-Creating the quarterly results report for the ExCo and SvB
